abstract: >
  The Cartesian root-mean-square deviation (RMSD) of atomic coordinates is a fundamental metric
  for comparing three-dimensional molecular structures. This work introduces the permutation-
  invariant RMSD (iRMSD) to handle molecular symmetry and atom-permutations more robustly,
  enabling efficient conformational pruning in automated computational chemistry workflows.
